&lt;p&gt;Job Purpose:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Business Operations Executive to oversee day-to-day office operations and provide essential support to both local Vietnamese staff and expatriates. This role is pivotal in ensuring smooth business processes and fostering a welcoming environment for employees navigating a new office in a new country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Accountabilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage general office administration, facilities, and vendor coordination.&lt;br&gt;Human Resources administration and filing.&lt;br&gt;Act as a primary resource for expatriates, offering orientation and guidance on local practices, cultural nuances, and essential services.&lt;br&gt;Assist staff with navigating business processes and compliance requirements.&lt;br&gt;Support onboarding and integration for new employees, ensuring a seamless transition.&lt;br&gt;Maintain effective communication between local and international teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications, Experience, &amp;amp; Skills:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Fluent in English (spoken and written).&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Previous experience working for a multinational company in Vietnam.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Strong organisational skills and business acumen.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Excellent interpersonal skills with the ability to guide and support diverse teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Competencies:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross-cultural communication: Ability to bridge cultural differences and foster collaboration.&lt;br&gt;Problem-solving and adaptability: &amp;nbsp;Skilled at resolving challenges and adjusting to changing circumstances.&lt;br&gt;Attention to detail: Ensures accuracy in office operations and compliance processes.&lt;br&gt;Customer service orientation: Provides proactive support to staff and expatriates.&lt;br&gt;Time management and prioritisation: Handles multiple tasks efficiently.&lt;br&gt;Discretion and confidentiality: &amp;nbsp;Maintains professionalism in sensitive matters&lt;br&gt;Ensures full compliance with country legal expectations and company policies and procedures including adherence to all GDPR requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;dmg events is an equal opportunity employer. If you have not had feedback from us within 14 days, please consider your application as unsuccessful for this round.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Conference Manager’s responsibility is to support the Conference Director in delivering all aspects of the conference, including agenda, speaker management and relationships within the industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Manage relationships with industry leaders, partner organisations, vendors, and media&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Programme research and development&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Speaker acquisition&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;On-site delivery that strengthens speaker, attendee and sponsor relationships&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Market intelligence to identify new content opportunities&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Manage the call for papers process and session selection for the technical conference&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Accountabilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support Conference Director in:&lt;/p&gt;
