&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;dmg events is an international exhibitions and publishing company. We attract more than 650,000+ visitors to our global portfolio of 115+ exhibitions each year. Through our global events, our aim is simple: we want to accelerate business through face-to-face events, which is why we work so hard to bring people together, creating opportunities for them to network, learn and do business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;dmg events is part of the Daily Mail Group Trust (DMGT). DMGT manages a diverse, multinational portfolio of companies with total revenues of £2bn, providing businesses and consumers with compelling information, analysis, insight, events, news, and entertainment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Purpose: &lt;/strong&gt;To lead, grow, and deliver a portfolio of events, driving long-term growth, commercial performance, and industry impact.The role holds full P&amp;amp;L accountability, including international and local sales delivery. Acts as the strategic leader of the allocated events, ensuring strong cross-functional alignment (Sales, Marketing, Content, Operations) while adapting event brands, content, and commercial strategy to meet local market needs.Key focus areas include local market development, stakeholder engagement, sales delivery, brand positioning, and identifying new event opportunities.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event Strategy and Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Lead the overall event strategy, ensuring long-term growth, market relevance, and competitive positioning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Develop and maintain a 3-year strategic plan for each event and market outlook in line with the Event Delivery Playbook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Use data, market intelligence, commercial insights, and customer feedback to shape event direction and growth initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Drive sustainable event growth, audience impact, and commercial performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ensure cross-functional alignment across Sales, Marketing, PR, Content, and Operations teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Lead and facilitate regular event meetings to ensure alignment on objectives, priorities, and performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Manage organisational complexity and competing priorities effectively while maintaining focus on strategic objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&amp;amp;L Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Own and manage the full event P&amp;amp;L, including revenue delivery, cost control, and profitability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Set, manage, and deliver event budgets and financial targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Monitor event performance against budget through regular reviews of revenue and costs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Establish and maintain monthly forecasting processes to determine projected event outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Provide accurate and timely reporting of event KPIs, forecasts, and financial performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Liaise with Finance to meet all financial reporting requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Achieve revenue and contribution targets in line with approved budgets and forecasts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ensure billing and collections are completed in accordance with contractual agreements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ensure all outstanding debtors are collected in full prior to the event.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Drive total sales performance across the event portfolio in collaboration with internal sales teams, agents, and local market channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Execute agreed sales and sponsorship strategies to achieve commercial objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Participate in meetings and negotiations with key customers, sponsors, and stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Monitor sales performance and ensure accurate reporting through Salesfo

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure a world class level of marketing that adopts a mix of traditional and innovative tactics and strategies that reflects the position of the events. This role will be expected to plan and implement marketing campaigns across the events within the portfolio. &amp;nbsp;Events include but not limited to: Global Rail and Trips Summit 2027.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Accountabilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create and implement an integrated marketing campaign for the entire exhibition including exhibitor, delegate and visitor campaigns&lt;br&gt;Develop marketing plan for lead generation and engage with each team to ensure optimum marketing for each aspect of the event&lt;br&gt;Forecast and monitor entire budget, marketing timeline and media plan&lt;br&gt;Use the full marketing mix to promote the exhibition and conferences in accordance with the marketing strategy from utilising below and above the line mediums including email, direct mail, PR, social media, outdoor advertising, digital marketing, trade and daily advertising, SMS/Whats app, website, radio, search engine marketing and TV.&lt;br&gt;Manage the clean, verification and build of the show database&lt;br&gt;Negotiate and manage barter details with appropriate media partners and associations&lt;br&gt;Ensure show websites are fully up to date with latest information. Manage the integration of any third-party modules (e.g. floorplanner, show APP, etc.) between suppliers.&lt;br&gt;Utilise and manage digital tools (i.e. App, survey tool) to enhance campaigns.&lt;br&gt;Coordinate the design, production of all marketing collateral, including sales brochures, conference brochures, visitor tickets, post-cards, top line report, post-show report, print advertisements, web banners/emails, etc.&lt;br&gt;Manage PPC campaign, with support of Digital Marketing Executive – review results and make recommendations.&lt;br&gt;Provide onsite support to ensure the smooth running of marketing related activity (i.e. registration, press office, research, placement of branding and materials; sales stand).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Context:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role works closely with the event’s exhibition sales and sponsorship team, conference production team and the delegate sales team to generate leads and conversions. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications, Experience, &amp;amp; Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum Qualifications and Knowledge: &amp;nbsp; Marketing qualification is advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum Experience: 3+ years in mid manager level marketing, but not strictly in event marketing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job-Specific Skills:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Strategy creation and critical path analysis&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Experience in the use of databases in both mass and targeted direct marketing campaigns&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Experience managing the production of mobile apps and online registration systems&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;People management&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Website user experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Budget management, including budgetary responsibility for decision making relating to a wide variety of potential marketing channels&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Strong knowledge of MS Office Suite, including: MS Word, Outlook, and Excel&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to effectively communicate with and relate to all levels both within and outside the organisation &amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;dmg events is an international exhibitions and publishing company. We attract more than 425,000 visitors to our global portfolio of 80 exhibitions each year. Through our global events, our aim is simple. We want to accelerate business through face-to-face events, which is why we work so hard to bring people together, creating opportunities for them to network, learn and do business. dmg events is part of the Daily Mail Group Trust (DMGT). DMGT Manages a diverse, multinational portfolio of companies with total revenues of £2bn, that provide businesses and consumers with compelling information, analysis, insight, events, news, and entertainment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Purpose: &lt;/strong&gt;The Human Resources Director - MEAA is responsible for developing and executing the overall people strategy to support the division&#39;s business objectives. As a strategic business partner, the HR Director - MEAA will lead all aspects of human capital management, including talent acquisition, divisional development, employee engagement, performance management, learning &amp;amp; development, rewards, culture, and HR operations. Operating within a dynamic and fast-paced events business, this role will ensure the division attracts, develops, and retains high-performing talent while fostering an agile, collaborative, and high-performance culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Accountabilities:&lt;br&gt;Strategic HR Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement the organization&#39;s HR strategy aligned with business goals and growth plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a trusted advisor to the executive leadership team on all people-related matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive organizational design and workforce planning to support evolving business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead change management initiatives during business transformation and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop succession planning and leadership development strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talent Acquisition &amp;amp; Workforce Planning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop talent acquisition strategies to attract high-quality professionals across event operations, commercial, creative, production, and corporate functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong employer branding initiatives to position the organization as an employer of choice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with business leaders on manpower planning and hiring forecasts.&lt;/li&gt;
